'''Auxerre – Branches Aerodrome''' ({{lang-fr|Aérodrome d'Auxerre - Branches}}<ref name="UAF" />) {{airport codes|AUF<ref name="GCM" /><ref>{{cite web | url = http://aviation-safety.net/database/airport/airport.php?id=AUF | title = Auxerre-Branches Airport (AUF / LFLA) | publisher = [[Aviation Safety Network]] | accessdate = 12 May 2010}}</ref>|LFLA}} is an [[airport]] serving [[Auxerre]] and [[Branches, Yonne|Branches]], both ''[[Communes of France|communes]]'' of the [[Yonne]] [[Departments of France|department]]<ref name="AIP" /> in the [[Bourgogne]] [[Regions of France|region]] of [[France]]. The airport is located {{convert|8.5|km|NM|1|abbr=on|lk=on}} northwest of Auxerre<ref name="AIP" /> and approximately {{convert|4|km|NM|1|abbr=on}} southeast of Branches.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.wikimapia.org/#lat=47.8343616&lon=3.5084152&z=12&l=0&m=b&v=8&gz=0;34809494;477967823;995636;0;157928;511749;0;854937 | title = Aerial image with distances to airport from Auxerre and Branches | publisher = WikiMapia | accessdate = 12 May 2010}}</ref>
==Facilities== The airport resides at an [[elevation]] of {{convert|523|ft|0}} above [[mean sea level]]. It has one [[runway]] designated 01/19 with an [[asphalt]] surface measuring {{convert|1650|x|30|m|0}}.<ref name="AIP" />
